Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Place the courgettes in a baking tray with the thyme, soaked mushrooms and olive oil and season well.Roast in the oven for 15 minutes.For the chilli scrambled eggs, melt the butter in a non-stick frying pan. Add the eggs, chilli, saffron and mushroom water and cook for two minutes.Stir in the cream and season.Serve the roasted courgettes alongside the chilli eggs.